The paper proposes a new framework for partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) in multi-agent systems (MASs) that involves the impact of agents on each other's reputations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves planning algorithms for agents to select optimal actions in stochastic MASs, which could fall under the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves modeling the effects of reputation in interactions, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
